description: Reductant Pressure too High: Component or system operation obstructed or blocked
correction:
Arrived at machine. Hooked up to machine and pulled codes.
 Codes showed inactive but ran a bit and went active. Looked
 up codes in Prosis and began checking possible causes.
 Found that DEF line clogged which caused pressure to go to
 high. Removed and replaced DEF feed line from pump to
 dosing valve injector due to following test to check if
 clog was removed. Tech tool operation 25847-3 SCR system
 drain. Pressure reading properly now. Performed service
 regen. Cleared all codes. R

description: Reductant Injection Air Pressure Control Valve Control: Actuator stuck closed
correction: hookup to unit via TT2- unit has several issues. P208A86 reductant pump signal invalid active, full derate active as well as low system voltage with key on, engine not running. Remove covers on batteries and verified low voltage - 10.2 vdc on each battery. Started unit and found that alternator is putting out 28vdc @ 36.5 amps. Wet spots on battery caps / check electrolyte level - tested capacity w/ batt. tester (each rated at 1400 cca); batt 1: 530CCA , batt 2: 416CCA. Could not shut unit down

The Venturi tube was cleaned and the inputs on the AGR differential pressure transmitter were checked. description: Engine ECU - Engine oil temperature: Current below normal or open circuit
correction:
Checked this error in Prosis and found below symptoms and possible causes:

Symptom:
○	Machine may be difficult to start in cold weather
Possible causes:
○	Signal line short-circuited to higher voltage
○	Open circuit

As per the above symptoms, we have checked the below points:
1. Signal line short-circuited to a higher voltage, found okay.
2. Checked for open circuit, and found that the connector is loosened.
3. Removed the connector, cleaned it, and fitted it back properly.
4. Star

correction:

○ V-ECU function can not work correctly

○ Defective alternator
○ Defective battery, battery cables
○ Loose connection

12/8/20 K1R1 A40G SN342579 HRS3530

chain. found the nox sensors wasn't
reading at spec was low at 206. change out both nox
sensors. run thru a regen and passed with no issues. update
chain on findings. chain wanted to do other checks, we
checked over exhaust for leaks, pulled diff pressure sensor
off and had moisture there and venturi. update chain on
findings and said its showing egr seems not to be working
correctly. wants us to have them run again and see if codes
come back. put a parts list together for the egr valve etc.
clean up for day.

grab parts etc and return parts and gather information on
unit. locate truck. pull venturi tube off and inspect parts
and egr cooler. egr cooler is dry. replace bad diff
pressure sensor. found egr valve not opening and closing
correct. pull egr valve off. drill out spacers for bo

description: P20E797 - Aftertreatment Control ModuleReductant Injection Air Pressure too High: Component or system operation obstructed or blocked
correction:
1. Symptom = Occurred errors_(P204F93 / P20E797)
2. Root cause = Blocked dosing valve
3. Diagnosis & Action
 - Repeated drop the air pressure_(300 kPA ~ 0 kPA)
 - pressure valve & air pipe = OK status
 - Dosing valve exchange_(40 ~ 50 kPA in idle status)

description: Reductant Quality: Circuit short to ground
correction: Vces technician arrived onsite and found p206a11 to have 4 inactive counts. I hooked up the laptop, I updated software and removed the front belt cover. I removed the def armature connector and tested the wiring. I wiggled the wiring but wasn't able to get the def quality to change. I researched the system and determined there must be a internal error in the new def tank armature.  REMOVED THE COUNTERWEIGHT ASSEMBLY. DROPPED THE DEF AND FUEL TANK. REPLACED THE DEF ARMATURE. LIFTED DEF AND FUEL
